reviewText:
LOVE. LOVE. LOVE. These. Tees.
1) Love the bamboo viscose fiber (soft, drape, substantial weight);
2)  Fits the Mid-Riffish area (particularly forgiving while still being neat and tidy at the shoulder);
3) Fits the shoulders perfectly (as many of you know, you often get sloppy, drooping shoulders when trying to size up for the mid-riffish issue);
4) Actually fits my upper arms (with room to spare!);
5) Beautiful cut, very flattering on a less than perfect figure (I was surprised to find the XL is perfect - I am usually a 1x);
6) They wash beautifully with no obvious shrinkage;
7) LOVE the dark charcoal grey and black which are true and deep (My only complaint is that they don't offer a navy, and the black sells out quickly. The other colors all look like pastel PJs to me). I'd buy dozens of these if I could get some classic white, ecru and navy for my basic staple wardrobe.

BTW, I also have the sleep shirt -- and I LOVE it also. But be forewarned -- the SLEEP TEE is a narrower fit than this V-neck tee. I'd size up one in the sleep tee.

My only concern is the absolutely heinous smell emanating from these items before washing. I know that many fabrics are pressed with formaldehyde or other chemicals before shipping. This smells x1000 worse. I'm wondering if it is a bug repellent of some sort to keep the tees safe during their travels over from China? Also, that reminds me. I'd pay double to have these made in any democratic, non-slave-labor country. Seriously. Otherwise -- love the tees.  (OH, and, I contacted the company directly 6mos ago when they seemed to run out of XL black tees......(crickets).....no response from customer service. Ever. Oh well. Good thing they have an excellent tee.
